An Act to protect assisted living residents from unfair and deceptive billing practices.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 14 of chapter 19D of the General Laws, as appearing in 2024
2 Official Edition, is hereby amended by inserting at the end thereof the following sentence:- “A
3 required notice period to terminate a written residency agreement shall not be enforceable upon
4 the death of a resident. Upon the death of a resident, a sponsor shall provide not less than 10
5 days for the removal of personal belongings without charges, expenses, or other assessments
6 otherwise due under a written residency agreement.”.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect immediately upon passage.
